		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Binghamton</placeName> <date>June 21<hi rend="sup">st</hi> 1860</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#44;</p>
				<p>Dear friend&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">As the Advertise&#45;<lb/>ment in the Occident inserted<lb/> for my benefit has effected<lb/> naught in all this time&#59; it appears<lb/> to me useless to continue it longer.<lb/>  Permit me again to thank you<lb/> for having inserted it. <del>and</del> Please<lb/> inform me of the amt of my<lb/> indebtedness.  Should you at any<lb/> time hear of any family residing in<lb/> a healthy&#44; pleasant&#44; location where<lb/> I might find a desirable home&#44;<lb/> I shall be greatly obliged to you&#44;<lb/> to apprise me of it.  I think<lb/> at any rate of remaining here this<lb/> summer as I would not like<lb/> to <sic>undergoe</sic> the fatigue of<lb/> packing &#38; traveling during the<lb/> warm season.  I have the plea&#45;<lb/>sure of having my sister <persName>Julia</persName>&#44;</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>with me at present.  She arrived<lb/> yesterday.  I hope your health<lb/> is good.  With best wishes for<lb/> your health and happiness</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Yours with much esteem and<lb/> respect.</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">R. A. Lazarus</persName></p>
		</body>
